sentences: Lambert Ferri (fl. c. 1250–1300) was a trouvère and cleric at the Benedictine monastery at Saint-Léonard, Pas-de-Calais.
By 1268 he was a canon and a deacon of the monastery; he is last associated with the monastery in 1282.
